 informs people's conduct, he charts a new course for ethnography that seeks to integrate the study of the emotions into anthropological analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAffect (Psychology) 0aAffect (Psychology). 0aEmotions. 0aEthnopsychologyxPapua New GuineaxGazelle Peninsula. 0aEthnopsychologyzPapua New GuineazGazelle Peninsula. 0aPhilosophy, Tolai. 0aTolai (Melanesian people)xPsychology. 0aTolai (Melanesian people)xSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press eBook Package Archivez978311063534840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520911642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520911642.jpg  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press eBook Package Archive  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles